<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>old school • old school tie</xh5><p> <i>old school—</i>said of conservative or old-fashioned views and principles: My grandmother, who was of the <u>old school</u>, said that self-praise was half slander.</p><p> <i>old school tie</i>—(UK) the clannish loyalty of people who knew each other at public school or a university: The Inspector was tacitly accusing him of favoring his own class—of shielding an “old school tie.”</p> </entry>
